# Solution Architect — Reusable Prompt Library

A token-efficient toolkit for documenting an undocumented microservices estate
(~10 FE + BE services under one root folder).

## How to use this file

1. **Once per codebase:** run the extraction commands (§0), paste their output
   into the manifest prompt (§1), save the result as `manifest.txt`.
2. **Every session afterward:** paste `manifest.txt` at the top, then paste the
   prompt for the task you want.
3. Every prompt ends with a format constraint (`... only. No prose.`) — that line
   is what keeps output tokens low. Don't remove it.
4. Iterate in **deltas**: when fixing one service, share only that section and say
   "update only X". Never re-paste a whole document.

---

## 0. Extract raw material from source code

Run from the root folder. Output is messy — you don't read it, you feed it to §1.

```bash
# List all projects
ls -d */

# Dependency files (Node)
find . -name package.json -not -path "*/node_modules/*" \
  -exec echo "=== {} ===" \; -exec cat {} \;

# Dependency files (Java/Spring)
find . -name pom.xml -exec echo "=== {} ===" \; -exec cat {} \;

# Inter-service calls + messaging
grep -rn "http://\|https://\|KafkaTemplate\|@KafkaListener\|kafka" \
  --include=*.js --include=*.java --include=*.ts . | grep -v node_modules

# DB / cache connections
grep -rni "jdbc:\|mongodb://\|postgres\|redis\|DATABASE_URL" \
  --include=*.yml --include=*.properties --include=*.env* . | grep -v node_modules
```

