## 1. Generate the manifest  *(run once)*

> Paste the raw command output from §0 above this prompt.

```
Below is raw output from a microservices codebase — dependency
files (package.json/pom.xml), inter-service call patterns, and
DB/infra configs across ~10 projects under one root folder.

Build a compact SERVICE MANIFEST from it.

Format — one line per service:
<name>(FE/BE): <responsibility> | <tech> | <store> | deps: <a,b,c>

Rules:
- Infer FE/BE from dependencies (React/Angular = FE, server
  framework = BE).
- Infer responsibility from project name + route/controller hints.
- "store" = DB/cache found in config (postgres, redis, mongo).
  "none" if stateless.
- "deps" = other internal services it calls + Kafka topics/queues.
- Mark any inferred-but-uncertain value with (?).
- Use short codes: BE/FE, svc, deps.

Output the manifest ONLY. No headings, no prose, no explanation.
```

After generating: skim every `(?)` and verify against code before trusting it.

